# RTK Token Optimization Rules

Always use RTK commands to minimize token consumption by 60-90%.

## Git Commands
- Use `rtk git status` instead of `git status`
- Use `rtk git diff` instead of `git diff`
- Use `rtk git log` instead of `git log`
- Use `rtk git add` instead of `git add`
- Use `rtk git commit` instead of `git commit`
- Use `rtk git push` instead of `git push`
- Use `rtk git pull` instead of `git pull`

## File Operations
- Use `rtk read <file>` instead of `cat <file>`
- Use `rtk ls` instead of `ls -la`
- Use `rtk grep <pattern>` instead of `grep`
- Use `rtk find` instead of `find`

## Build & Test
- Use `rtk cargo test` instead of `cargo test`
- Use `rtk cargo build` instead of `cargo build`
- Use `rtk npm test` instead of `npm test`

## Why
RTK filters command output to compress tokens by 60-90% before reaching Claude's context window. This saves significant tokens on large projects.

## Example
Instead of: `git status` (outputs ~2000 tokens)
Use: `rtk git status` (outputs ~200 tokens, -90% savings)